sub_title: MSc Political Science at Leiden University
summary: My main areas of expertise are in quantitative and qualitative research, and in academic event management and coordination. My areas of interest in research include social and economic sustainability, behavioural economics and game theory. I have experience working with various levels of seniority, and with different types of clients through my internships and past work experiences. I thrive in problem solving whether it be in team leadership offering creative logistical or theoretical solutions, or in political science research. I am currently open to job opportunities as a research assistant, as well as in organisations that aim to answer questions relating to ethics, sustainability or human rights issues.
